<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Kero:
[B]Ya know, I may only have been a cleric for 41 levels, but I've been in EQ for almost a year, and have never been  on a single raid.

Guess what people, Raiding ISN'T the only part of the game.  Yeah, yeah, then someone comes back with, "Well, raiding is what high level people do for fun!  And since there are more high level people, that's why raiding counts."  Um, ok, so the AA exp groups don't count for anything?  Grinding in Seb, KC, etc?  Those aren't a big part of the game?  

I can hear it now.. "Well, once you've maxed AA then all you can do is raid!"  I'll give you that.  But I'd like to see some solid numbers (and yes, Verant can pull the data without compromising account information) on how many characters are full up in exp in 60, and have maxed their AA points!  And once planes of power, where they plan to "further character progression".  

Yes, CH may have unbalanced the Raid game in the Clerics favor.  

Druid vs. Cleric, soloing.  Winner: Druid.
Druid vs. Cleric, travelling.  Winner:  Druid
Druid vs. Cleric, exp grinding:  Winner:  Druid (Yes, we have better heals, but they have better utility, can do more all around for a group)
Druid vs. Cleric, raiding:  Winner:  Cleric
Druid vs. Cleric, making money: Winner:  Tie

IMNSHO, It's not the cleric class that's over powered.  And I will be very upset if they give CH to another class.  Give them a 2k heal for about 600 mana.  And if you do that, then give us invis and self-only sow (We wouldn't need ports then).  Give us a disease based dot that works on all things, but make it a step or two down from druids.  

That balancing, I could live with.  

And yeah, so what if I don't know what I'm talking about... never stopped me before!  ;)[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
